{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351525868,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fcda78001YhiescXPia757n","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01R3Xs488YBNZeNdoPtiJVex","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/features/check.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/features/check.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * features/check.ts — Validate the features file for schema issues, broken deps, and orphans.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage:\n5:  *   wombo features check\n6:  *\n7:  * Checks:\n8:  *   - Required fields present on every feature\n9:  *   - No duplicate IDs\n10:  *   - All depends_on references point to existing features\n11:  *   - No circular dependencies\n12:  *   - No orphaned subtasks (subtask IDs unique)\n13:  *   - Priority/difficulty values are valid enums\n14:  *   - Effort strings are parseable ISO 8601 durations\n15:  */\n16: \n17: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\n18: import {\n19:   loadFeatures,\n20:   allFeatureIds,\n21:   parseDurationMinutes,\n22:   type Feature,\n23:   type Subtask,\n24:   type FeaturesFile,\n25:   type Priority,\n26:   type Difficulty,\n27:   type FeatureStatus,\n28: } from \"../../lib/features.js\";\n29: \n30: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n31: // Types\n32: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n33: \n34: export interface FeaturesCheckOptions {\n35:   projectRoot: string;\n36:   config: WomboConfig;\n37: }\n38: \n39: interface CheckResult {\n40:   errors: string[];\n41:   warnings: string[];\n42: }\n43: \n44: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n45: // Validation\n46: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n47: \n48: const VALID_STATUSES: FeatureStatus[] = [\n49:   \"backlog\", \"planned\", \"in_progress\", \"blocked\", \"in_review\", \"done\", \"cancelled\",\n50: ];\n51: \n52: const VALID_PRIORITIES: Priority[] = [\"critical\", \"high\", \"medium\", \"low\", \"wishlist\"];\n53: \n54: const VALID_DIFFICULTIES: Difficulty[] = [\"trivial\", \"easy\", \"medium\", \"hard\", \"very_hard\"];\n55: \n56: function collectAllItems(data: FeaturesFile): (Feature | Subtask)[] {\n57:   const items: (Feature | Subtask)[] = [];\n58:   const collect = (list: (Feature | Subtask)[]) => {\n59:     for (const item of list) {\n60:       items.push(item);\n61:       if (item.subtasks?.length) collect(item.subtasks);\n62:     }\n63:   };\n64:   collect(data.features ?? []);\n65:   collect(data.archive ?? []);\n66:   return items;\n67: }\n68: \n69: function checkFeatures(data: FeaturesFile): CheckResult {\n70:   const errors: string[] = [];\n71:   const warnings: string[] = [];\n72:   const allItems = collectAllItems(data);\n73:   const allIds = allItems.map((i) => i.id);\n74:   const idSet = new Set<string>();\n75: \n76:   // Check for duplicates\n77:   for (const id of allIds) {\n78:     if (idSet.has(id)) {\n79:       errors.push(`Duplicate ID: \"${id}\"`);\n80:     }\n81:     idSet.add(id);\n82:   }\n83: \n84:   // Check each item\n85:   for (const item of allItems) {\n86:     const prefix = `[${item.id}]`;\n87: \n88:     // Required fields\n89:     if (!item.id) errors.push(`${prefix} Missing required field: id`);\n90:     if (!item.title) errors.push(`${prefix} Missing required field: title`);\n91:     if (!item.status) errors.push(`${prefix} Missing required field: status`);\n92: \n93:     // Validate enum values\n94:     if (item.status && !VALID_STATUSES.includes(item.status)) {\n95:       errors.push(`${prefix} Invalid status: \"${item.status}\"`);\n96:     }\n97:     if (item.priority && !VALID_PRIORITIES.includes(item.priority)) {\n98:       errors.push(`${prefix} Invalid priority: \"${item.priority}\"`);\n99:     }\n100:     if (item.difficulty && !VALID_DIFFICULTIES.includes(item.difficulty)) {\n101:       errors.push(`${prefix} Invalid difficulty: \"${item.difficulty}\"`);\n102:     }\n103: \n104:     // Validate effort\n105:     if (item.effort) {\n106:       const minutes = parseDurationMinutes(item.effort);\n107:       if (minutes === Infinity) {\n108:         warnings.push(`${prefix} Unparseable effort duration: \"${item.effort}\"`);\n109:       }\n110:     }\n111: \n112:     // Check depends_on references\n113:     if (item.depends_on?.length) {\n114:       for (const dep of item.depends_on) {\n115:         if (!idSet.has(dep)) {\n116:           errors.push(`${prefix} Broken dependency: \"${dep}\" does not exist`);\n117:         }\n118:       }\n119:     }\n120:   }\n121: \n122:   // Check for circular dependencies (simple DFS)\n123:   const visited = new Set<string>();\n124:   const visiting = new Set<string>();\n125:   const depMap = new Map<string, string[]>();\n126:   for (const item of allItems) {\n127:     depMap.set(item.id, item.depends_on ?? []);\n128:   }\n129: \n130:   function hasCycle(id: string): boolean {\n131:     if (visiting.has(id)) return true;\n132:     if (visited.has(id)) return false;\n133:     visiting.add(id);\n134:     for (const dep of depMap.get(id) ?? []) {\n135:       if (hasCycle(dep)) {\n136:         errors.push(`Circular dependency detected involving: \"${id}\" → \"${dep}\"`);\n137:         return true;\n138:       }\n139:     }\n140:     visiting.delete(id);\n141:     visited.add(id);\n142:     return false;\n143:   }\n144: \n145:   for (const id of idSet) {\n146:     hasCycle(id);\n147:   }\n148: \n149:   // Warn about features with no effort estimate\n150:   for (const item of allItems) {\n151:     if (!item.effort || item.effort === \"PT0S\") {\n152:       warnings.push(`[${item.id}] No effort estimate`);\n153:     }\n154:   }\n155: \n156:   return { errors, warnings };\n157: }\n158: \n159: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n160: // Command\n161: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n162: \n163: export async function cmdFeaturesCheck(opts: FeaturesCheckOptions): Promise<void> {\n164:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n165: \n166:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n167:   const result = checkFeatures(data);\n168: \n169:   const allItems = collectAllItems(data);\n170:   console.log(`\\nChecking ${config.featuresFile} (${allItems.length} items)...\\n`);\n171: \n172:   if (result.errors.length === 0 && result.warnings.length === 0) {\n173:     console.log(\"  All checks passed. No issues found.\");\n174:     return;\n175:   }\n176: \n177:   if (result.errors.length > 0) {\n178:     console.log(`  ERRORS (${result.errors.length}):`);\n179:     for (const e of result.errors) {\n180:       console.log(`    \\x1b[31m✗\\x1b[0m ${e}`);\n181:     }\n182:     console.log(\"\");\n183:   }\n184: \n185:   if (result.warnings.length > 0) {\n186:     console.log(`  WARNINGS (${result.warnings.length}):`);\n187:     for (const w of result.warnings) {\n188:       console.log(`    \\x1b[33m⚠\\x1b[0m ${w}`);\n189:     }\n190:     console.log(\"\");\n191:   }\n192: \n193:   if (result.errors.length > 0) {\n194:     process.exit(1);\n195:   }\n196: }\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/features/check.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * features/check.ts — Validate the features file for schema issues, broken deps, and orphans.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   wombo features check\n *\n * Checks:\n *   - Required fields present on every feature\n *   - No duplicate IDs\n *   - All depends_on references point to existing features\n *   - No circular dependencies\n *   - No orphaned subtasks (subtask IDs unique)\n *   - Priority/difficulty values are valid enums\n *   - Effort strings are parseable ISO 8601 durations\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\nimport {\n  loadFeatures,\n  allFeatureIds,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351525865,"end":1773351525867}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351526253,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fcddea001aE7Zo0IvpNFXq8","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01D6tuwtVW3zv6FTymam9JEC","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/features/archive.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/features/archive.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * features/archive.ts — Move done/cancelled features to the archive section.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage:\n5:  *   wombo features archive              # archive all done + cancelled\n6:  *   wombo features archive <feature-id> # archive a specific feature\n7:  *   wombo features archive --dry-run    # show what would be archived\n8:  */\n9: \n10: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\n11: import {\n12:   loadFeatures,\n13:   saveFeatures,\n14:   findFeatureById,\n15:   type Feature,\n16: } from \"../../lib/features.js\";\n17: \n18: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n19: // Types\n20: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n21: \n22: export interface FeaturesArchiveOptions {\n23:   projectRoot: string;\n24:   config: WomboConfig;\n25:   featureId?: string;\n26:   dryRun?: boolean;\n27: }\n28: \n29: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n30: // Command\n31: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n32: \n33: export async function cmdFeaturesArchive(opts: FeaturesArchiveOptions): Promise<void> {\n34:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n35: \n36:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n37: \n38:   // Ensure archive array exists\n39:   if (!data.archive) {\n40:     data.archive = [];\n41:   }\n42: \n43:   let toArchive: Feature[];\n44: \n45:   if (opts.featureId) {\n46:     // Archive a specific feature\n47:     const idx = data.features.findIndex((f) => f.id === opts.featureId);\n48:     if (idx === -1) {\n49:       // Check if already in archive\n50:       if (data.archive.find((f) => f.id === opts.featureId)) {\n51:         console.log(`Feature \"${opts.featureId}\" is already in the archive.`);\n52:         return;\n53:       }\n54:       console.error(`Feature \"${opts.featureId}\" not found.`);\n55:       process.exit(1);\n56:       return;\n57:     }\n58:     toArchive = [data.features[idx]];\n59:   } else {\n60:     // Archive all done + cancelled features\n61:     toArchive = data.features.filter(\n62:       (f) => f.status === \"done\" || f.status === \"cancelled\"\n63:     );\n64:   }\n65: \n66:   if (toArchive.length === 0) {\n67:     console.log(\"No features to archive.\");\n68:     return;\n69:   }\n70: \n71:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n72:     console.log(`\\nWould archive ${toArchive.length} feature(s):\\n`);\n73:     for (const f of toArchive) {\n74:       console.log(`  ${f.id} — ${f.title} (${f.status})`);\n75:     }\n76:     return;\n77:   }\n78: \n79:   // Move features from active to archive\n80:   const archiveIds = new Set(toArchive.map((f) => f.id));\n81:   data.features = data.features.filter((f) => !archiveIds.has(f.id));\n82:   data.archive.push(...toArchive);\n83: \n84:   saveFeatures(projectRoot, config, data);\n85: \n86:   console.log(`\\nArchived ${toArchive.length} feature(s):`);\n87:   for (const f of toArchive) {\n88:     console.log(`  ${f.id} — ${f.title} (${f.status})`);\n89:   }\n90: }\n\n(End of file - total 90 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/features/archive.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * features/archive.ts — Move done/cancelled features to the archive section.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   wombo features archive              # archive all done + cancelled\n *   wombo features archive <feature-id> # archive a specific feature\n *   wombo features archive --dry-run    # show what would be archived\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../../config.js\";\nimport {\n  loadFeatures,\n  saveFeatures,\n  findFeatureById,\n  type Feature,\n} from \"../../lib/features.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Types\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351526245,"end":1773351526252}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351526774,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fcdf66001DMlHUldGRGc0p1","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_019QVCWhgvfQ23SJdZ1tufjF","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/status.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/status.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * status.ts — Show the status of the current wave.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: wombo status\n5:  *\n6:  * Loads the wave state, checks for dead processes, and prints a dashboard.\n7:  */\n8: \n9: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n10: import { loadState, saveState, updateAgent } from \"../lib/state.js\";\n11: import { isProcessRunning } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\n12: import { printDashboard } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\n13: \n14: export interface StatusOptions {\n15:   projectRoot: string;\n16:   config: WomboConfig;\n17: }\n18: \n19: export async function cmdStatus(opts: StatusOptions): Promise<void> {\n20:   const state = loadState(opts.projectRoot);\n21:   if (!state) {\n22:     console.log(\"No active wave. Use 'wombo launch' to start one.\");\n23:     return;\n24:   }\n25: \n26:   // Update running agent status from process state\n27:   for (const agent of state.agents) {\n28:     if (agent.status === \"running\" && agent.pid) {\n29:       if (!isProcessRunning(agent.pid)) {\n30:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n31:           status: \"completed\",\n32:           completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n33:         });\n34:       }\n35:     }\n36:   }\n37:   saveState(opts.projectRoot, state);\n38: \n39:   printDashboard(state);\n40: }\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/status.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * status.ts — Show the status of the current wave.\n *\n * Usage: wombo status\n *\n * Loads the wave state, checks for dead processes, and prints a dashboard.\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport { loadState, saveState, updateAgent } from \"../lib/state.js\";\nimport { isProcessRunning } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\nimport { printDashboard } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\n\nexport interface StatusOptions {\n  projectRoot: string;\n  config: WomboConfig;\n}\n\nexport async function cmdStatus(opts: StatusOptions): Promise<void> {\n  const state = loadState(opts.projectRoot);","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351526772,"end":1773351526774}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351527288,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fce175001gOYe1f3uXdXSc2","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01A88gqkUzQ2Jt3oiGUV9uPi","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/launch.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/launch.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * launch.ts — Launch a wave of agents.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: wombo launch [selection options] [launch options]\n5:  *\n6:  * This is the primary entry point for starting a new wave. It selects features\n7:  * from the features file, creates a wave state, sets up worktrees, and launches\n8:  * agent processes (either headless or interactive via tmux).\n9:  *\n10:  * IMPORTANT: This file also exports shared helper functions that are reused\n11:  * by resume.ts and other commands:\n12:  *   - launchSingleHeadless\n13:  *   - handleBuildVerification\n14:  *   - handleRetry\n15:  *   - launchNextQueued\n16:  */\n17: \n18: import { execSync } from \"node:child_process\";\n19: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n20: import type { Feature, SelectionOptions, Priority, Difficulty } from \"../lib/features.js\";\n21: import { loadFeatures, selectFeatures, parseDurationMinutes, saveFeatures } from \"../lib/features.js\";\n22: import {\n23:   loadState,\n24:   saveState,\n25:   createWaveState,\n26:   createAgentState,\n27:   updateAgent,\n28:   activeAgents,\n29:   queuedAgents,\n30:   isWaveComplete,\n31:   type WaveState,\n32:   type AgentState,\n33: } from \"../lib/state.js\";\n34: import {\n35:   createWorktree,\n36:   installDeps,\n37:   featureBranchName,\n38:   worktreePath,\n39:   worktreeReady,\n40:   branchHasChanges,\n41:   removeWorktree,\n42:   log as wtLog,\n43: } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\n44: import { generatePrompt, generateConflictResolutionPrompt } from \"../lib/prompt.js\";\n45: import {\n46:   launchHeadless,\n47:   retryHeadless,\n48:   launchInteractive,\n49:   retryInteractive,\n50:   launchConflictResolver,\n51:   isProcessRunning,\n52: } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\n53: import { ProcessMonitor } from \"../lib/monitor.js\";\n54: import { runBuild } from \"../lib/verifier.js\";\n55: import { mergeBranch, mergeBaseIntoFeature, pushBaseBranch } from \"../lib/merger.js\";\n56: import {\n57:   printDashboard,\n58:   printFeatureSelection,\n59:   printAgentUpdate,\n60: } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\n61: import { WomboTUI } from \"../lib/tui.js\";\n62: import { ensureAgentDefinition } from \"../lib/templates.js\";\n63: \n64: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n65: // Types\n66: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n67: \n68: export interface LaunchCommandOptions {\n69:   projectRoot: string;\n70:   config: WomboConfig;\n71:   // Selection\n72:   topPriority?: number;\n73:   quickestWins?: number;\n74:   priority?: Priority;\n75:   difficulty?: Difficulty;\n76:   features?: string[];\n77:   allReady?: boolean;\n78:   // Launch\n79:   maxConcurrent: number;\n80:   model?: string;\n81:   interactive: boolean;\n82:   dryRun: boolean;\n83:   baseBranch: string;\n84:   maxRetries: number;\n85:   noTui: boolean;\n86:   autoPush: boolean;\n87: }\n88: \n89: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n90: // Shared Helpers (exported for resume.ts and others)\n91: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n92: \n93: /**\n94:  * Mark a feature as done in the features file after a successful merge.\n95:  * Updates status to \"done\", completion to 100, and sets ended_at.\n96:  *\n97:  * GUARD: Verifies that the feature branch has actually been merged into\n98:  * baseBranch before allowing the status change. This prevents callers\n99:  * from accidentally marking verified-but-unmerged features as done.\n100:  */\n101: export function markFeatureDone(\n102:   projectRoot: string,\n103:   featureId: string,\n104:   config: WomboConfig,\n105:   baseBranch: string\n106: ): void {\n107:   try {\n108:     // Verify the feature branch was actually merged into base\n109:     const branch = featureBranchName(featureId, config);\n110:     try {\n111:       execSync(`git merge-base --is-ancestor \"${branch}\" \"${baseBranch}\"`, {\n112:         cwd: projectRoot,\n113:         stdio: \"pipe\",\n114:       });\n115:     } catch {\n116:       // git merge-base --is-ancestor exits non-zero if NOT an ancestor\n117:       console.error(\n118:         `Warning: ${featureId} branch \"${branch}\" is not merged into \"${baseBranch}\" — refusing to mark as done`\n119:       );\n120:       return;\n121:     }\n122: \n123:     const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n124:     const feature = data.features.find((f) => f.id === featureId);\n125:     if (feature && feature.status !== \"done\") {\n126:       feature.status = \"done\";\n127:       feature.completion = 100;\n128:       feature.ended_at = new Date().toISOString();\n129:       saveFeatures(projectRoot, config, data);\n130:     }\n131:   } catch (err: any) {\n132:     // Non-fatal — log but don't crash the wave\n133:     console.error(`Warning: failed to update feature status for ${featureId}: ${err.message}`);\n134:   }\n135: }\n136: \n137: /**\n138:  * Launch a single agent in headless mode.\n139:  * Sets up worktree, installs deps, generates prompt, launches agent process.\n140:  */\n141: export async function launchSingleHeadless(\n142:   projectRoot: string,\n143:   state: WaveState,\n144:   agent: AgentState,\n145:   feature: Feature,\n146:   monitor: ProcessMonitor,\n147:   config: WomboConfig,\n148:   model?: string\n149: ): Promise<void> {\n150:   updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n151:     status: \"installing\",\n152:     started_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n153:     activity: \"setting up worktree...\",\n154:   });\n155:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n156: \n157:   try {\n158:     // Skip worktree setup if already ready (resume case)\n159:     if (worktreeReady(agent.worktree)) {\n160:       wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"worktree already exists, skipping setup\");\n161:     } else {\n162:       // Create worktree (async — doesn't block other agents)\n163:       await createWorktree(projectRoot, feature.id, state.base_branch, config);\n164: \n165:       // Install dependencies (async)\n166:       updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"installing deps...\" });\n167:       await installDeps(agent.worktree, feature.id, config);\n168:     }\n169: \n170:     // Generate prompt\n171:     const prompt = generatePrompt(feature, state.base_branch, config);\n172: \n173:     // Launch agent\n174:     wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"launching agent...\");\n175:     const result = launchHeadless({\n176:       worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n177:       featureId: feature.id,\n178:       prompt,\n179:       model,\n180:       config,\n181:     });\n182: \n183:     updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n184:       status: \"running\",\n185:       pid: result.pid,\n186:       activity: \"starting...\",\n187:     });\n188:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n189: \n190:     monitor.addProcess(feature.id, result.process);\n191:     wtLog(agent.feature_id, `running (PID: ${result.pid})`);\n192:   } catch (err: any) {\n193:     updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n194:       status: \"failed\",\n195:       error: err.message,\n196:       activity: null,\n197:       completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n198:     });\n199:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n200:     wtLog(agent.feature_id, `SETUP FAILED: ${err.message.split(\"\\n\")[0]}`);\n201:   }\n202: }\n203: \n204: /**\n205:  * Handle build verification after agent completion.\n206:  * Runs build, auto-merges on pass, retries on failure if retries remain.\n207:  *\n208:  * ASYNC — runs build and merge without blocking the event loop.\n209:  */\n210: export async function handleBuildVerification(\n211:   projectRoot: string,\n212:   state: WaveState,\n213:   agent: AgentState,\n214:   feature: Feature,\n215:   config: WomboConfig,\n216:   model?: string,\n217:   monitor?: ProcessMonitor\n218: ): Promise<void> {\n219:   try {\n220:     printAgentUpdate(agent, \"verifying build...\");\n221: \n222:     const buildResult = await runBuild(agent.worktree, config);\n223: \n224:     if (buildResult.passed) {\n225:       updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n226:         status: \"verified\",\n227:         build_passed: true,\n228:         build_output: null,\n229:       });\n230:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n231:       printAgentUpdate(agent, `BUILD PASSED (${Math.round(buildResult.durationMs / 1000)}s)`);\n232: \n233:       // Auto-merge: attempt merge + conflict resolution\n234:       await attemptMerge(projectRoot, state, agent, feature, config, model);\n235:     } else {\n236:       if (agent.retries < agent.max_retries) {\n237:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n238:           status: \"retry\",\n239:           retries: agent.retries + 1,\n240:           build_passed: false,\n241:           build_output: buildResult.errorSummary,\n242:         });\n243:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n244:         printAgentUpdate(\n245:           agent,\n246:           `BUILD FAILED — retrying (${agent.retries}/${agent.max_retries})`\n247:         );\n248: \n249:         // Retry with build errors\n250:         if (agent.session_id) {\n251:           const retryResult = retryHeadless({\n252:             worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n253:             featureId: agent.feature_id,\n254:             sessionId: agent.session_id,\n255:             buildErrors: buildResult.errorSummary,\n256:             model,\n257:             config,\n258:           });\n259: \n260:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n261:             status: \"running\",\n262:             pid: retryResult.pid,\n263:           });\n264:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n265: \n266:           // Add retry process to monitor so events are tracked\n267:           if (monitor) {\n268:             monitor.addProcess(agent.feature_id, retryResult.process);\n269:           }\n270:         }\n271:       } else {\n272:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n273:           status: \"failed\",\n274:           build_passed: false,\n275:           build_output: buildResult.errorSummary,\n276:           error: `Build failed after ${agent.max_retries} retries`,\n277:           completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n278:         });\n279:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n280:         printAgentUpdate(agent, \"BUILD FAILED — max retries reached\");\n281:       }\n282:     }\n283:   } catch (err: any) {\n284:     // Catch-all — never let build verification crash the process\n285:     printAgentUpdate(agent, `VERIFY ERROR: ${err.message?.slice(0, 100)}`);\n286:     updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n287:       status: \"failed\",\n288:       error: `Build verification error: ${err.message}`,\n289:       completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n290:     });\n291:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n292:   }\n293: }\n294: \n295: /**\n296:  * Attempt to merge a verified agent's branch into the base branch.\n297:  *\n298:  * Handles conflict detection, base-into-feature merge, and resolver agent\n299:  * launch. Extracted from handleBuildVerification so it can be called\n300:  * independently (e.g., from resume's sequential merge phase).\n301:  */\n302: export async function attemptMerge(\n303:   projectRoot: string,\n304:   state: WaveState,\n305:   agent: AgentState,\n306:   feature: Feature,\n307:   config: WomboConfig,\n308:   model?: string,\n309: ): Promise<void> {\n310:   printAgentUpdate(agent, \"auto-merging...\");\n311:   try {\n312:     const mergeResult = await mergeBranch(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch, config);\n313: \n314:     if (mergeResult.success) {\n315:       updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n316:         status: \"merged\",\n317:         completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n318:       });\n319:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n320:       printAgentUpdate(agent, `MERGED (${mergeResult.commitHash?.slice(0, 7)})`);\n321: \n322:       // Mark feature as done in .features.yml so it won't be re-selected\n323:       markFeatureDone(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, config, state.base_branch);\n324: \n325:       // Clean up worktree after successful merge\n326:       try {\n327:         removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, true);\n328:         printAgentUpdate(agent, \"worktree and branch removed\");\n329:       } catch {\n330:         // Not critical — worktree cleanup is best-effort\n331:       }\n332:     } else {\n333:       // Merge failed — attempt automatic conflict resolution\n334:       const mergeError = mergeResult.error ?? \"Unknown merge error\";\n335:       printAgentUpdate(agent, `MERGE CONFLICT — attempting resolution...`);\n336: \n337:       try {\n338:         // Merge base INTO the feature worktree to create conflict markers\n339:         const conflictResult = await mergeBaseIntoFeature(\n340:           agent.worktree,\n341:           state.base_branch,\n342:           config\n343:         );\n344: \n345:         if (conflictResult.error && !conflictResult.conflicting) {\n346:           printAgentUpdate(agent, `CONFLICT SETUP FAILED: ${conflictResult.error.slice(0, 100)}`);\n347:           return; // Leave as \"verified\" for manual resolution\n348:         }\n349: \n350:         if (!conflictResult.conflicting) {\n351:           // Base merged cleanly into feature — retry merge into base.\n352:           printAgentUpdate(agent, \"base merged cleanly into feature — retrying merge...\");\n353:           const retryMerge = await mergeBranch(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch, config);\n354:           if (retryMerge.success) {\n355:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n356:               status: \"merged\",\n357:               completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n358:             });\n359:             saveState(projectRoot, state);\n360:             printAgentUpdate(agent, `MERGED after rebase (${retryMerge.commitHash?.slice(0, 7)})`);\n361:             markFeatureDone(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, config, state.base_branch);\n362:             try {\n363:               removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, true);\n364:             } catch {}\n365:             return;\n366:           }\n367: \n368:           // Retry still failed — launch resolver agent\n369:           printAgentUpdate(agent, `retry merge still failed — launching resolver agent...`);\n370: \n371:           const secondConflict = await mergeBaseIntoFeature(\n372:             agent.worktree,\n373:             state.base_branch,\n374:             config\n375:           );\n376: \n377:           const conflictFiles = secondConflict.conflicting\n378:             ? secondConflict.files\n379:             : [\"(unknown — merge direction mismatch)\"];\n380:           const resolverMergeError = retryMerge.error ?? mergeError;\n381: \n382:           await launchResolverAndRetryMerge(\n383:             projectRoot, state, agent, feature, config, model,\n384:             resolverMergeError, conflictFiles\n385:           );\n386:           return;\n387:         }\n388: \n389:         // There are real conflicts — launch a resolver agent\n390:         printAgentUpdate(\n391:           agent,\n392:           `${conflictResult.files.length} conflicting file(s): ${conflictResult.files.join(\", \")}`\n393:         );\n394: \n395:         await launchResolverAndRetryMerge(\n396:           projectRoot, state, agent, feature, config, model,\n397:           mergeError, conflictResult.files\n398:         );\n399:       } catch (conflictErr: any) {\n400:         printAgentUpdate(agent, `CONFLICT RESOLUTION ERROR: ${conflictErr.message?.slice(0, 100)}`);\n401:         // Leave as \"verified\" for manual resolution\n402:       }\n403:     }\n404:   } catch (mergeErr: any) {\n405:     printAgentUpdate(agent, `AUTO-MERGE ERROR: ${mergeErr.message?.slice(0, 100)}`);\n406:   }\n407: }\n408: \n409: /**\n410:  * Launch a conflict resolver agent, wait for it to finish, re-verify build,\n411:  * and retry the merge. Extracted to avoid duplicating the resolver flow.\n412:  */\n413: async function launchResolverAndRetryMerge(\n414:   projectRoot: string,\n415:   state: WaveState,\n416:   agent: AgentState,\n417:   feature: Feature,\n418:   config: WomboConfig,\n419:   model: string | undefined,\n420:   mergeError: string,\n421:   conflictFiles: string[]\n422: ): Promise<void> {\n423:   const conflictPrompt = generateConflictResolutionPrompt(\n424:     feature,\n425:     state.base_branch,\n426:     mergeError,\n427:     config\n428:   );\n429: \n430:   updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n431:     status: \"resolving_conflict\",\n432:     activity: `resolving ${conflictFiles.length} conflict(s)...`,\n433:   });\n434:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n435: \n436:   const resolverResult = launchConflictResolver({\n437:     worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n438:     featureId: agent.feature_id,\n439:     prompt: conflictPrompt,\n440:     model,\n441:     config,\n442:   });\n443: \n444:   updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n445:     pid: resolverResult.pid,\n446:   });\n447:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n448: \n449:   // Wait for the resolver process to complete, then re-verify and retry merge.\n450:   // We intentionally do NOT add the resolver to the ProcessMonitor because\n451:   // the monitor's onComplete callback would trigger handleBuildVerification\n452:   // again, causing infinite recursion. Instead we await the process directly.\n453:   const resolverExitCode = await new Promise<number | null>((resolve) => {\n454:     resolverResult.process.on(\"exit\", (code) => resolve(code));\n455:     resolverResult.process.on(\"error\", () => resolve(null));\n456:   });\n457: \n458:   printAgentUpdate(agent, `conflict resolver exited (code ${resolverExitCode}) — re-verifying build...`);\n459: \n460:   // Re-verify build after conflict resolution\n461:   const rebuildResult = await runBuild(agent.worktree, config);\n462: \n463:   if (!rebuildResult.passed) {\n464:     printAgentUpdate(agent, `POST-CONFLICT BUILD FAILED`);\n465:     updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n466:       status: \"failed\",\n467:       build_passed: false,\n468:       build_output: rebuildResult.errorSummary,\n469:       error: \"Build failed after conflict resolution\",\n470:       completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n471:     });\n472:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n473:     return;\n474:   }\n475: \n476:   printAgentUpdate(agent, \"post-conflict build passed — retrying merge...\");\n477: \n478:   const retryMerge = await mergeBranch(\n479:     projectRoot,\n480:     agent.branch,\n481:     state.base_branch,\n482:     config\n483:   );\n484: \n485:   if (retryMerge.success) {\n486:     updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n487:       status: \"merged\",\n488:       build_passed: true,\n489:       completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n490:     });\n491:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n492:     printAgentUpdate(agent, `MERGED after conflict resolution (${retryMerge.commitHash?.slice(0, 7)})`);\n493:     markFeatureDone(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, config, state.base_branch);\n494:     try {\n495:       removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, true);\n496:     } catch {}\n497:   } else {\n498:     printAgentUpdate(agent, `POST-CONFLICT MERGE FAILED: ${retryMerge.error}`);\n499:     updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n500:       status: \"failed\",\n501:       error: `Merge still failed after conflict resolution: ${retryMerge.error}`,\n502:       completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n503:     });\n504:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n505:   }\n506: }\n507: \n508: /**\n509:  * Handle retry of a failed agent (error-based, not build-based).\n510:  */\n511: export function handleRetry(\n512:   projectRoot: string,\n513:   state: WaveState,\n514:   agent: AgentState,\n515:   monitor: ProcessMonitor,\n516:   config: WomboConfig,\n517:   model?: string\n518: ): void {\n519:   if (!agent.session_id || !agent.error) return;\n520: \n521:   const retryResult = retryHeadless({\n522:     worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n523:     featureId: agent.feature_id,\n524:     sessionId: agent.session_id,\n525:     buildErrors: agent.error,\n526:     model,\n527:     config,\n528:   });\n529: \n530:   updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n531:     status: \"running\",\n532:     pid: retryResult.pid,\n533:   });\n534:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n535: \n536:   monitor.addProcess(agent.feature_id, retryResult.process);\n537: }\n538: \n539: /**\n540:  * Launch the next queued agent if capacity allows.\n541:  */\n542: export function launchNextQueued(\n543:   projectRoot: string,\n544:   state: WaveState,\n545:   featureMap: Map<string, Feature>,\n546:   monitor: ProcessMonitor,\n547:   config: WomboConfig,\n548:   model?: string\n549: ): void {\n550:   const active = activeAgents(state);\n551:   const queued = queuedAgents(state);\n552: \n553:   if (active.length < state.max_concurrent && queued.length > 0) {\n554:     const next = queued[0];\n555:     const feature = featureMap.get(next.feature_id);\n556:     if (feature) {\n557:       launchSingleHeadless(projectRoot, state, next, feature, monitor, config, model);\n558:     }\n559:   }\n560: }\n561: \n562: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n563: // Headless Wave Launch\n564: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n565: \n566: async function launchWaveHeadless(\n567:   projectRoot: string,\n568:   state: WaveState,\n569:   features: Feature[],\n570:   opts: LaunchCommandOptions\n571: ): Promise<void> {\n572:   const { config, model } = opts;\n573:   const featureMap = new Map(features.map((f) => [f.id, f]));\n574: \n575:   const monitor = new ProcessMonitor(projectRoot, {\n576:     onSessionId: (featureId, sessionId) => {\n577:       updateAgent(state, featureId, { session_id: sessionId });\n578:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n579:     },\n580:     onComplete: (featureId) => {\n581:       updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n582:         status: \"completed\",\n583:         completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n584:       });\n585:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n586: \n587:       // Run build verification — fire-and-forget\n588:       const agent = state.agents.find((a) => a.feature_id === featureId)!;\n589:       handleBuildVerification(projectRoot, state, agent, featureMap.get(featureId)!, config, model, monitor)\n590:         .then(() => launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model))\n591:         .catch((err) => {\n592:           wtLog(featureId, `BUILD VERIFICATION UNHANDLED ERROR: ${err.message}`);\n593:           launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model);\n594:         });\n595:     },\n596:     onError: (featureId, error) => {\n597:       const agent = state.agents.find((a) => a.feature_id === featureId)!;\n598:       if (agent.retries < agent.max_retries) {\n599:         updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n600:           status: \"retry\",\n601:           retries: agent.retries + 1,\n602:           error,\n603:         });\n604:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n605: \n606:         // Retry\n607:         handleRetry(projectRoot, state, agent, monitor, config, model);\n608:       } else {\n609:         updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n610:           status: \"failed\",\n611:           error,\n612:           completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n613:         });\n614:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n615:       }\n616: \n617:       // Try to launch next queued agent\n618:       launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model);\n619:     },\n620:     onOutput: (_featureId, _data) => {\n621:       // Raw output — logged to file by ProcessMonitor\n622:     },\n623:     onActivity: (featureId, activity) => {\n624:       updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n625:         activity,\n626:         activity_updated_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n627:       });\n628:       // Don't save to disk on every activity — too frequent.\n629:     },\n630:   });\n631: \n632:   // Create the TUI — it will auto-refresh and show activity from the monitor\n633:   const tuiRef = { current: null as WomboTUI | null };\n634:   const startTUI = () => {\n635:     tuiRef.current = new WomboTUI({\n636:       state,\n637:       monitor,\n638:       projectRoot,\n639:       interactive: false,\n640:       config,\n641:       onQuit: () => {\n642:         // Same as SIGINT — save state and exit\n643:         for (const agent of state.agents) {\n644:           if (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n645:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"interrupted\" });\n646:           }\n647:         }\n648:         monitor.killAll();\n649:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n650:         console.log(\"State saved. Use 'wombo resume' to continue.\");\n651:         process.exit(0);\n652:       },\n653:     });\n654:     tuiRef.current.start();\n655:   };\n656: \n657:   // Handle graceful shutdown\n658:   process.on(\"SIGINT\", () => {\n659:     if (tuiRef.current) tuiRef.current.stop();\n660:     for (const agent of state.agents) {\n661:       if (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n662:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"interrupted\" });\n663:       }\n664:     }\n665:     monitor.killAll();\n666:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n667:     console.log(\"\\nState saved. Use 'wombo resume' to continue.\");\n668:     process.exit(0);\n669:   });\n670: \n671:   // Launch initial batch — set up worktrees in parallel\n672:   const tolaunch = queuedAgents(state).slice(0, opts.maxConcurrent);\n673:   console.log(`Setting up ${tolaunch.length} agent(s) in parallel...\\n`);\n674: \n675:   await Promise.all(\n676:     tolaunch.map((agent) =>\n677:       launchSingleHeadless(\n678:         projectRoot,\n679:         state,\n680:         agent,\n681:         featureMap.get(agent.feature_id)!,\n682:         monitor,\n683:         config,\n684:         model\n685:       )\n686:     )\n687:   );\n688: \n689:   const launched = state.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"running\").length;\n690: \n691:   // Start the TUI dashboard (or skip if --no-tui)\n692:   if (opts.noTui) {\n693:     console.log(`${launched} agent(s) running. (--no-tui mode, dashboard prints every 15s)\\n`);\n694:     printDashboard(state);\n695:   } else {\n696:     console.log(`${launched} agent(s) running. Launching TUI...\\n`);\n697:     startTUI();\n698:   }\n699: \n700:   // Background monitoring loop — checks for dead processes and launches queued\n701:   const POLL_INTERVAL = 5000;\n702:   let dashboardCounter = 0;\n703:   while (!isWaveComplete(state)) {\n704:     await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, POLL_INTERVAL));\n705: \n706:     // Check for completed processes that weren't caught by event handlers\n707:     for (const agent of state.agents) {\n708:       if (\n709:         (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") &&\n710:         agent.pid &&\n711:         !isProcessRunning(agent.pid) &&\n712:         !monitor.isRunning(agent.feature_id)\n713:       ) {\n714:         if (agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n715:           // Conflict resolver died — the await in handleBuildVerification\n716:           // will resolve via the 'exit' event, so nothing to do here\n717:           continue;\n718:         }\n719:         // Process exited but we didn't get a callback\n720:         // Check if the agent actually made any commits\n721:         if (!branchHasChanges(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch)) {\n722:           // Agent died without producing any code — mark as failed, not completed\n723:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n724:             status: \"failed\",\n725:             error: \"Agent process exited without making any commits\",\n726:             activity: null,\n727:             completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n728:           });\n729:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n730:           wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"process died with no code changes — marked failed\");\n731:         } else {\n732:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n733:             status: \"completed\",\n734:             completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n735:             activity: \"done\",\n736:           });\n737:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n738:           try {\n739:             await handleBuildVerification(projectRoot, state, agent, featureMap.get(agent.feature_id)!, config, model, monitor);\n740:           } catch (err: any) {\n741:             wtLog(agent.feature_id, `POLL VERIFY ERROR: ${err.message}`);\n742:           }\n743:         }\n744:         launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model);\n745:       }\n746:     }\n747: \n748:     // Persist state periodically\n749:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n750: \n751:     // Update TUI state reference (or print dashboard in --no-tui mode)\n752:     if (tuiRef.current) {\n753:       tuiRef.current.updateState(state);\n754:     } else if (opts.noTui) {\n755:       dashboardCounter++;\n756:       if (dashboardCounter % 3 === 0) {\n757:         printDashboard(state);\n758: \n759:         // Auto-push base branch if requested\n760:         if (opts.autoPush) {\n761:           const anyMerged = state.agents.some((a) => a.status === \"merged\");\n762:           if (anyMerged) {\n763:             await pushBaseBranch(projectRoot, state.base_branch, config);\n764:           } else {\n765:             console.log(\"No branches were merged — skipping push.\");\n766:           }\n767:         }\n768:       }\n769:     }\n770:   }\n771: \n772:   // Wave complete — tear down TUI and show final summary\n773:   if (tuiRef.current) tuiRef.current.stop();\n774:   printDashboard(state);\n775: \n776:   // Auto-push base branch if requested\n777:   if (opts.autoPush) {\n778:     await pushBaseBranch(projectRoot, state.base_branch, config);\n779:   }\n780: \n781:   console.log(\"Wave complete.\");\n782: }\n783: \n784: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n785: // Interactive Wave Launch\n786: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n787: \n788: async function launchWaveInteractive(\n789:   projectRoot: string,\n790:   state: WaveState,\n791:   features: Feature[],\n792:   opts: LaunchCommandOptions\n793: ): Promise<void> {\n794:   const { config, model } = opts;\n795:   const featureMap = new Map(features.map((f) => [f.id, f]));\n796: \n797:   // Show dashboard immediately\n798:   printDashboard(state);\n799: \n800:   // Launch initial batch in tmux — parallelize setup\n801:   const tolaunch = queuedAgents(state).slice(0, opts.maxConcurrent);\n802:   console.log(`Setting up ${tolaunch.length} agent(s) in parallel...\\n`);\n803: \n804:   await Promise.all(\n805:     tolaunch.map(async (agent) => {\n806:       updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n807:         status: \"installing\",\n808:         started_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n809:         activity: \"setting up worktree...\",\n810:       });\n811:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n812: \n813:       try {\n814:         if (worktreeReady(agent.worktree)) {\n815:           wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"worktree already exists, skipping setup\");\n816:         } else {\n817:           await createWorktree(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, state.base_branch, config);\n818:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"installing deps...\" });\n819:           await installDeps(agent.worktree, agent.feature_id, config);\n820:         }\n821: \n822:         const prompt = generatePrompt(\n823:           featureMap.get(agent.feature_id)!,\n824:           state.base_branch,\n825:           config\n826:         );\n827: \n828:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"launching tmux session...\");\n829:         const result = launchInteractive({\n830:           worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n831:           featureId: agent.feature_id,\n832:           prompt,\n833:           model,\n834:           interactive: true,\n835:           config,\n836:         });\n837: \n838:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n839:           status: \"running\",\n840:           pid: result.pid,\n841:           activity: \"tmux session active\",\n842:         });\n843:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n844:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, `tmux session: ${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-${agent.feature_id}`);\n845:       } catch (err: any) {\n846:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n847:           status: \"failed\",\n848:           error: err.message,\n849:           activity: null,\n850:           completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n851:         });\n852:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n853:         wtLog(agent.feature_id, `SETUP FAILED: ${err.message.split(\"\\n\")[0]}`);\n854:       }\n855:     })\n856:   );\n857: \n858:   console.log(\"\\nInteractive sessions launched. Use these commands:\");\n859:   console.log(`  tmux attach -t ${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-<feature-id>   # attach to a session`);\n860:   console.log(\"  tmux ls                                                  # list sessions\");\n861:   console.log(\"  wombo status                                             # check status\");\n862:   console.log(\"  wombo verify                                             # verify builds\");\n863:   console.log(\"  wombo merge                                              # merge verified\");\n864:   console.log(\"  wombo cleanup                                            # remove worktrees\");\n865: \n866:   printDashboard(state);\n867: }\n868: \n869: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n870: // Main Command\n871: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n872: \n873: export async function cmdLaunch(opts: LaunchCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n874:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n875: \n876:   console.log(\"\\n--- Wombo: Launch ---\\n\");\n877: \n878:   // Ensure agent definition exists — reinstall from template if missing\n879:   ensureAgentDefinition(projectRoot, config);\n880: \n881:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n882:   // Check for existing wave state — don't overwrite work in progress\n883:   // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n884:   const existingState = loadState(projectRoot);\n885:   if (existingState) {\n886:     const merged = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"merged\");\n887:     const verified = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"verified\");\n888:     const completed = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"completed\");\n889:     const running = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"running\");\n890:     const queued = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"queued\");\n891:     const failed = existingState.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"failed\");\n892: \n893:     const hasWork = merged.length > 0 || verified.length > 0 || completed.length > 0 || running.length > 0;\n894: \n895:     if (hasWork) {\n896:       console.log(`Existing wave found: ${existingState.wave_id}`);\n897:       console.log(`  ${merged.length} merged, ${verified.length} verified, ${completed.length} completed, ${running.length} running, ${queued.length} queued, ${failed.length} failed`);\n898: \n899:       // Finalize any merged agents by marking their features as done\n900:       if (merged.length > 0) {\n901:         console.log(\"\\nFinalizing merged features in .features.yml...\");\n902:         for (const agent of merged) {\n903:           markFeatureDone(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, config, existingState.base_branch);\n904:           // Clean up worktree and branch (already merged, safe to delete)\n905:           try {\n906:             removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, true);\n907:             console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: marked done, worktree removed`);\n908:           } catch {\n909:             console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: marked done (worktree already cleaned)`);\n910:           }\n911:         }\n912:       }\n913: \n914:       // Verified agents: build passed but NOT merged — do NOT mark done.\n915:       // Leave them for 'wombo resume' to attempt the merge.\n916:       if (verified.length > 0) {\n917:         for (const agent of verified) {\n918:           console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: verified (not yet merged) — use 'wombo resume' to merge`);\n919:         }\n920:       }\n921: \n922:       const activeCount = running.length + completed.length + queued.length;\n923:       if (activeCount > 0) {\n924:         console.error(`\\nWave ${existingState.wave_id} has ${activeCount} unfinished agent(s).`);\n925:         console.error(\"Use 'wombo resume' to continue the existing wave,\");\n926:         console.error(\"or 'wombo cleanup' to clear it before starting a new one.\");\n927:         process.exit(1);\n928:       }\n929: \n930:       // All agents are in terminal states (merged/verified/failed) — safe to start fresh\n931:       console.log(\"\\nAll agents in previous wave are finished. Starting fresh wave.\\n\");\n932:     }\n933:   }\n934: \n935:   // Load features\n936:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n937: \n938:   // Build selection options\n939:   const selOpts: SelectionOptions = {};\n940:   if (opts.topPriority) selOpts.topPriority = opts.topPriority;\n941:   if (opts.quickestWins) selOpts.quickestWins = opts.quickestWins;\n942:   if (opts.priority) selOpts.priority = opts.priority;\n943:   if (opts.difficulty) selOpts.difficulty = opts.difficulty;\n944:   if (opts.features) selOpts.featureIds = opts.features;\n945:   if (opts.allReady) selOpts.allReady = true;\n946: \n947:   // Select features\n948:   const selected = selectFeatures(data, selOpts);\n949: \n950:   if (selected.length === 0) {\n951:     if (opts.allReady) {\n952:       console.error(\n953:         \"No launchable features found. All features may be done, cancelled, or have unmet dependencies.\"\n954:       );\n955:     } else {\n956:       console.error(\n957:         \"No features matched the selection criteria. Use --all-ready to see all available.\"\n958:       );\n959:     }\n960:     process.exit(1);\n961:   }\n962: \n963:   // Show selection\n964:   printFeatureSelection(\n965:     selected.map((f) => ({\n966:       id: f.id,\n967:       title: f.title,\n968:       priority: f.priority,\n969:       difficulty: f.difficulty,\n970:       effort: f.effort,\n971:     }))\n972:   );\n973: \n974:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n975:     console.log(\"Dry run — not launching agents.\");\n976:     return;\n977:   }\n978: \n979:   // Create wave state\n980:   const state = createWaveState({\n981:     baseBranch: opts.baseBranch,\n982:     maxConcurrent: opts.maxConcurrent,\n983:     model: opts.model ?? null,\n984:     interactive: opts.interactive,\n985:   });\n986: \n987:   // Create agent entries for all selected features\n988:   for (const feature of selected) {\n989:     const branch = featureBranchName(feature.id, config);\n990:     const wtPath = worktreePath(projectRoot, feature.id, config);\n991:     const agent = createAgentState(feature.id, branch, wtPath, opts.maxRetries);\n992:     // Set effort estimate from feature spec\n993:     const effortMinutes = parseDurationMinutes(feature.effort);\n994:     agent.effort_estimate_ms = effortMinutes === Infinity ? null : effortMinutes * 60 * 1000;\n995:     state.agents.push(agent);\n996:   }\n997: \n998:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n999:   console.log(`Wave ${state.wave_id} created with ${selected.length} agents.`);\n1000: \n1001:   // Launch agents up to max_concurrent\n1002:   if (opts.interactive) {\n1003:     await launchWaveInteractive(projectRoot, state, selected, opts);\n1004:   } else {\n1005:     await launchWaveHeadless(projectRoot, state, selected, opts);\n1006:   }\n1007: }\n\n(End of file - total 1007 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/launch.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * launch.ts — Launch a wave of agents.\n *\n * Usage: wombo launch [selection options] [launch options]\n *\n * This is the primary entry point for starting a new wave. It selects features\n * from the features file, creates a wave state, sets up worktrees, and launches\n * agent processes (either headless or interactive via tmux).\n *\n * IMPORTANT: This file also exports shared helper functions that are reused\n * by resume.ts and other commands:\n *   - launchSingleHeadless\n *   - handleBuildVerification\n *   - handleRetry\n *   - launchNextQueued\n */\n\nimport { execSync } from \"node:child_process\";\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport type { Feature, SelectionOptions, Priority, Difficulty } from \"../lib/features.js\";","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351527284,"end":1773351527287}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351527723,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fce375001FJXdu2I5FQgajY","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01SErmhe8PMSN1znfjdLfjhR","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/cleanup.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/cleanup.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * cleanup.ts — Remove all wave-related resources.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: wombo cleanup\n5:  *\n6:  * Kills tmux sessions, removes worktrees, removes state and log files.\n7:  */\n8: \n9: import { existsSync, unlinkSync, rmSync } from \"node:fs\";\n10: import { execSync } from \"node:child_process\";\n11: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n12: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n13: import { killAllTmuxSessions } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\n14: import { cleanupAllWorktrees } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\n15: \n16: export interface CleanupOptions {\n17:   projectRoot: string;\n18:   config: WomboConfig;\n19:   dryRun?: boolean;\n20: }\n21: \n22: export async function cmdCleanup(opts: CleanupOptions): Promise<void> {\n23:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n24: \n25:   // Dry-run: show what would be cleaned up without doing it\n26:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n27:     console.log(\"\\n[dry-run] Would perform the following cleanup:\\n\");\n28: \n29:     // List tmux sessions that would be killed\n30:     try {\n31:       const sessions = execSync(\"tmux list-sessions -F '#{session_name}'\", {\n32:         encoding: \"utf-8\",\n33:       }).trim();\n34:       const prefix = config.agent.tmuxPrefix;\n35:       const matching = sessions\n36:         .split(\"\\n\")\n37:         .filter((s) => s.startsWith(prefix));\n38:       console.log(`  tmux sessions to kill: ${matching.length}`);\n39:       for (const s of matching) {\n40:         console.log(`    ${s}`);\n41:       }\n42:     } catch {\n43:       console.log(\"  tmux sessions to kill: 0 (no tmux server running)\");\n44:     }\n45: \n46:     // List worktrees that would be removed\n47:     try {\n48:       const worktrees = execSync(\"git worktree list --porcelain\", {\n49:         cwd: projectRoot,\n50:         encoding: \"utf-8\",\n51:       }).trim();\n52:       const prefix = config.git.worktreePrefix;\n53:       const matching = worktrees\n54:         .split(\"\\n\")\n55:         .filter((line) => line.startsWith(\"worktree \") && line.includes(prefix))\n56:         .map((line) => line.replace(\"worktree \", \"\"));\n57:       console.log(`  worktrees to remove: ${matching.length}`);\n58:       for (const w of matching) {\n59:         console.log(`    ${w}`);\n60:       }\n61:     } catch {\n62:       console.log(\"  worktrees to remove: 0\");\n63:     }\n64: \n65:     const statePath = resolve(projectRoot, \".wombo-state.json\");\n66:     const logDir = resolve(projectRoot, \".wombo-logs\");\n67:     if (existsSync(statePath)) console.log(\"  Would remove: .wombo-state.json\");\n68:     if (existsSync(logDir)) console.log(\"  Would remove: .wombo-logs/\");\n69: \n70:     return;\n71:   }\n72: \n73:   console.log(\"\\n--- Wombo: Cleanup ---\\n\");\n74: \n75:   // Kill tmux sessions\n76:   const killed = killAllTmuxSessions(config);\n77:   console.log(`Killed ${killed} tmux session(s)`);\n78: \n79:   // Remove worktrees\n80:   const removed = cleanupAllWorktrees(projectRoot, config);\n81:   console.log(`Removed ${removed} worktree(s)`);\n82: \n83:   // List remaining feature branches\n84:   try {\n85:     const branchPattern = `\"${config.git.branchPrefix}*\"`;\n86:     const branches = execSync(`git branch --list ${branchPattern}`, {\n87:       cwd: projectRoot,\n88:       encoding: \"utf-8\",\n89:     }).trim();\n90:     if (branches) {\n91:       console.log(`\\nRemaining feature branches:\\n${branches}`);\n92:       console.log('Use \"git branch -D <branch>\" to remove manually.');\n93:     }\n94:   } catch {}\n95: \n96:   // Remove state file\n97:   const statePath = resolve(projectRoot, \".wombo-state.json\");\n98:   if (existsSync(statePath)) {\n99:     unlinkSync(statePath);\n100:     console.log(\"Removed .wombo-state.json\");\n101:   }\n102: \n103:   // Remove log directory\n104:   const logDir = resolve(projectRoot, \".wombo-logs\");\n105:   if (existsSync(logDir)) {\n106:     rmSync(logDir, { recursive: true, force: true });\n107:     console.log(\"Removed .wombo-logs/\");\n108:   }\n109: \n110:   console.log(\"\\nCleanup complete.\");\n111: }\n\n(End of file - total 111 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/cleanup.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * cleanup.ts — Remove all wave-related resources.\n *\n * Usage: wombo cleanup\n *\n * Kills tmux sessions, removes worktrees, removes state and log files.\n */\n\nimport { existsSync, unlinkSync, rmSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { execSync } from \"node:child_process\";\nimport { resolve } from \"node:path\";\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport { killAllTmuxSessions } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\nimport { cleanupAllWorktrees } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\n\nexport interface CleanupOptions {\n  projectRoot: string;\n  config: WomboConfig;\n  dryRun?: boolean;\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351527720,"end":1773351527722}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351528169,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fce52900152MtRZOlqwWlqE","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01H816QkpvhaKB8kFyh3Kek9","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/verify.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/verify.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * verify.ts — Run build verification on completed agents.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: wombo verify [feature-id]\n5:  *\n6:  * Runs the build command in each completed agent's worktree. If a specific\n7:  * feature-id is given, verifies only that agent. Otherwise verifies all\n8:  * agents with status \"completed\".\n9:  */\n10: \n11: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n12: import { loadFeatures } from \"../lib/features.js\";\n13: import { loadState, saveState } from \"../lib/state.js\";\n14: import { printDashboard } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\n15: import { handleBuildVerification } from \"./launch.js\";\n16: \n17: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n18: // Types\n19: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n20: \n21: export interface VerifyCommandOptions {\n22:   projectRoot: string;\n23:   config: WomboConfig;\n24:   featureId?: string;\n25:   model?: string;\n26:   maxRetries?: number;\n27: }\n28: \n29: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n30: // Command\n31: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n32: \n33: export async function cmdVerify(opts: VerifyCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n34:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n35: \n36:   const state = loadState(projectRoot);\n37:   if (!state) {\n38:     console.log(\"No active wave.\");\n39:     return;\n40:   }\n41: \n42:   const toVerify = opts.featureId\n43:     ? state.agents.filter((a) => a.feature_id === opts.featureId)\n44:     : state.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"completed\");\n45: \n46:   if (toVerify.length === 0) {\n47:     console.log(\"No agents to verify.\");\n48:     return;\n49:   }\n50: \n51:   console.log(`\\nVerifying ${toVerify.length} agent(s)...\\n`);\n52: \n53:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n54: \n55:   for (const agent of toVerify) {\n56:     const feature = data.features.find((f) => f.id === agent.feature_id);\n57:     if (!feature) continue;\n58: \n59:     await handleBuildVerification(projectRoot, state, agent, feature, config, opts.model);\n60:   }\n61: \n62:   printDashboard(state);\n63: }\n\n(End of file - total 63 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/verify.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * verify.ts — Run build verification on completed agents.\n *\n * Usage: wombo verify [feature-id]\n *\n * Runs the build command in each completed agent's worktree. If a specific\n * feature-id is given, verifies only that agent. Otherwise verifies all\n * agents with status \"completed\".\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport { loadFeatures } from \"../lib/features.js\";\nimport { loadState, saveState } from \"../lib/state.js\";\nimport { printDashboard } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\nimport { handleBuildVerification } from \"./launch.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Types\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351528166,"end":1773351528169}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351528725,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fce6e7001do4Av77RQP0MlD","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01BhUYJBLq2CJGR2eeXVnNZx","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/merge.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/merge.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * merge.ts — Merge verified branches into the base branch.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: wombo merge [feature-id]\n5:  *\n6:  * Merges all verified agents (or a specific one) into the base branch.\n7:  * After merging, cleans up the worktree as best-effort.\n8:  */\n9: \n10: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n11: import {\n12:   loadState,\n13:   saveState,\n14:   updateAgent,\n15: } from \"../lib/state.js\";\n16: import { mergeBranch, pushBaseBranch } from \"../lib/merger.js\";\n17: import { removeWorktree } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\n18: import { printDashboard, printAgentUpdate } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\n19: \n20: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n21: // Types\n22: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n23: \n24: export interface MergeCommandOptions {\n25:   projectRoot: string;\n26:   config: WomboConfig;\n27:   featureId?: string;\n28:   autoPush?: boolean;\n29:   dryRun?: boolean;\n30: }\n31: \n32: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n33: // Command\n34: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n35: \n36: export async function cmdMerge(opts: MergeCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n37:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n38: \n39:   const state = loadState(projectRoot);\n40:   if (!state) {\n41:     console.log(\"No active wave.\");\n42:     return;\n43:   }\n44: \n45:   const toMerge = opts.featureId\n46:     ? state.agents.filter(\n47:         (a) => a.feature_id === opts.featureId && a.status === \"verified\"\n48:       )\n49:     : state.agents.filter((a) => a.status === \"verified\");\n50: \n51:   if (toMerge.length === 0) {\n52:     console.log(\"No verified agents to merge.\");\n53:     return;\n54:   }\n55: \n56:   // Dry-run: show what would be merged without merging\n57:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n58:     console.log(`\\n[dry-run] Would merge ${toMerge.length} branch(es):\\n`);\n59:     for (const agent of toMerge) {\n60:       console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id} — branch: ${agent.branch}`);\n61:     }\n62:     if (opts.autoPush) {\n63:       console.log(`\\n  Would push ${state.base_branch} to remote after merge.`);\n64:     }\n65:     return;\n66:   }\n67: \n68:   console.log(`\\nMerging ${toMerge.length} branch(es)...\\n`);\n69: \n70:   for (const agent of toMerge) {\n71:     printAgentUpdate(agent, \"merging...\");\n72:     const result = await mergeBranch(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch, config);\n73: \n74:     if (result.success) {\n75:       updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n76:         status: \"merged\",\n77:       });\n78:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n79:       printAgentUpdate(agent, `MERGED (${result.commitHash?.slice(0, 7)})`);\n80: \n81:       // Clean up worktree\n82:       try {\n83:         removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, false);\n84:         printAgentUpdate(agent, \"worktree removed\");\n85:       } catch {\n86:         // Not critical\n87:       }\n88:     } else {\n89:       printAgentUpdate(agent, `MERGE FAILED: ${result.error}`);\n90:     }\n91:   }\n92: \n93:   // Auto-push if requested\n94:   if (opts.autoPush) {\n95:     const anyMerged = state.agents.some((a) => a.status === \"merged\");\n96:     if (anyMerged) {\n97:       await pushBaseBranch(projectRoot, state.base_branch, config);\n98:     }\n99:   }\n100: \n101:   printDashboard(state);\n102: }\n\n(End of file - total 102 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/merge.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * merge.ts — Merge verified branches into the base branch.\n *\n * Usage: wombo merge [feature-id]\n *\n * Merges all verified agents (or a specific one) into the base branch.\n * After merging, cleans up the worktree as best-effort.\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport {\n  loadState,\n  saveState,\n  updateAgent,\n} from \"../lib/state.js\";\nimport { mergeBranch, pushBaseBranch } from \"../lib/merger.js\";\nimport { removeWorktree } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\nimport { printDashboard, printAgentUpdate } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351528721,"end":1773351528725}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351529086,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fce913001Q9SgI5tECbPLg6","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01Tws448TVPT3VAYFRARv22G","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/resume.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/resume.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * resume.ts — Resume a previously stopped wave.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: wombo resume [options]\n5:  *\n6:  * Restores from .wombo-state.json:\n7:  *   - Agents in \"running\"/\"installing\" whose PID is dead → re-check or re-launch\n8:  *   - Agents in \"queued\" → launch them\n9:  *   - Agents in terminal states (verified/failed/merged) → leave alone\n10:  */\n11: \n12: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n13: import type { Feature } from \"../lib/features.js\";\n14: import { loadFeatures } from \"../lib/features.js\";\n15: import {\n16:   loadState,\n17:   saveState,\n18:   updateAgent,\n19:   queuedAgents,\n20:   isWaveComplete,\n21:   type WaveState,\n22:   type AgentState,\n23: } from \"../lib/state.js\";\n24: import {\n25:   createWorktree,\n26:   installDeps,\n27:   worktreeReady,\n28:   worktreeExists,\n29:   branchHasChanges,\n30:   removeWorktree,\n31:   log as wtLog,\n32: } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\n33: import { generatePrompt } from \"../lib/prompt.js\";\n34: import {\n35:   launchInteractive,\n36:   isProcessRunning,\n37: } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\n38: import { ProcessMonitor } from \"../lib/monitor.js\";\n39: import { pushBaseBranch } from \"../lib/merger.js\";\n40: import { runBuild } from \"../lib/verifier.js\";\n41: import { printDashboard, printAgentUpdate } from \"../lib/ui.js\";\n42: import { WomboTUI } from \"../lib/tui.js\";\n43: import {\n44:   launchSingleHeadless,\n45:   handleBuildVerification,\n46:   handleRetry,\n47:   launchNextQueued,\n48:   markFeatureDone,\n49:   attemptMerge,\n50: } from \"./launch.js\";\n51: \n52: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n53: // Types\n54: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n55: \n56: export interface ResumeCommandOptions {\n57:   projectRoot: string;\n58:   config: WomboConfig;\n59:   maxConcurrent?: number;\n60:   model?: string;\n61:   interactive: boolean;\n62:   noTui: boolean;\n63:   autoPush: boolean;\n64:   baseBranch?: string;\n65:   maxRetries?: number;\n66: }\n67: \n68: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n69: // Command\n70: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n71: \n72: export async function cmdResume(opts: ResumeCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n73:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n74: \n75:   const state = loadState(projectRoot);\n76:   if (!state) {\n77:     console.error(\"No wave state found. Use 'wombo launch' to start a new wave.\");\n78:     process.exit(1);\n79:     return; // unreachable — helps TypeScript narrow\n80:   }\n81: \n82:   console.log(`\\n--- Wombo: Resume ${state.wave_id} ---\\n`);\n83: \n84:   // Load feature data for prompt generation\n85:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n86:   const featureMap = new Map(data.features.map((f) => [f.id, f]));\n87: \n88:   // Triage agents by current state\n89:   let toRelaunch: AgentState[] = [];\n90:   let toVerify: AgentState[] = [];\n91: \n92:   for (const agent of state.agents) {\n93:     switch (agent.status) {\n94:       case \"running\":\n95:       case \"installing\":\n96:       case \"retry\":\n97:       case \"resolving_conflict\":\n98:         // Was in-flight when we stopped — check if PID is still alive\n99:         if (agent.pid && isProcessRunning(agent.pid)) {\n100:           console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: still running (PID ${agent.pid}), leaving alone`);\n101:         } else {\n102:           // Process is dead — check if worktree exists with meaningful changes.\n103:           // Use worktreeExists (not worktreeReady) because node_modules may be\n104:           // missing — the worktree still has code that should be verified.\n105:           if (worktreeExists(agent.worktree) && branchHasChanges(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch)) {\n106:             // Worktree exists AND branch has commits — try build verification\n107:             console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: process dead, worktree has changes — will verify build`);\n108:             toVerify.push(agent);\n109:           } else {\n110:             // No worktree, or worktree exists but branch has no commits (agent did nothing)\n111:             const reason = worktreeExists(agent.worktree)\n112:               ? \"worktree exists but no code changes\"\n113:               : \"no worktree\";\n114:             console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: process dead, ${reason} — will re-launch`);\n115:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n116:               status: \"queued\",\n117:               pid: null,\n118:               activity: null,\n119:               session_id: null,\n120:             });\n121:             toRelaunch.push(agent);\n122:           }\n123:         }\n124:         break;\n125: \n126:       case \"queued\":\n127:         console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: queued — will launch`);\n128:         toRelaunch.push(agent);\n129:         break;\n130: \n131:       case \"completed\":\n132:         // Completed but not verified — verify\n133:         console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: completed — will verify build`);\n134:         toVerify.push(agent);\n135:         break;\n136: \n137:       case \"verified\":\n138:         // Build passed but NOT yet merged — need to attempt merge (+ conflict resolution)\n139:         console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: verified — will attempt merge`);\n140:         toVerify.push(agent);\n141:         break;\n142: \n143:       case \"merged\":\n144:         console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: merged — marking feature as done`);\n145:         markFeatureDone(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, config, state.base_branch);\n146:         try {\n147:           removeWorktree(projectRoot, agent.worktree, true);\n148:           console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: worktree and branch removed`);\n149:         } catch {\n150:           // Already cleaned — not critical\n151:         }\n152:         break;\n153: \n154:       case \"failed\":\n155:         // If the worktree exists with code changes and retries remain,\n156:         // attempt build verification rather than discarding the work.\n157:         if (agent.retries < agent.max_retries &&\n158:             worktreeExists(agent.worktree) &&\n159:             branchHasChanges(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch)) {\n160:           console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: failed but has work (retry ${agent.retries}/${agent.max_retries}) — will verify build`);\n161:           // Clear stale error and mark as completed so handleBuildVerification\n162:           // processes it correctly (it expects a non-failed agent)\n163:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n164:             status: \"completed\",\n165:             error: null,\n166:             build_passed: null,\n167:             build_output: null,\n168:             completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n169:           });\n170:           toVerify.push(agent);\n171:         } else if (agent.retries < agent.max_retries) {\n172:           // No worktree or no changes — re-launch from scratch\n173:           console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: failed, no salvageable work (retry ${agent.retries}/${agent.max_retries}) — will re-launch`);\n174:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n175:             status: \"queued\",\n176:             pid: null,\n177:             error: null,\n178:             build_passed: null,\n179:             build_output: null,\n180:             activity: null,\n181:             session_id: null,\n182:             completed_at: null,\n183:           });\n184:           toRelaunch.push(agent);\n185:         } else {\n186:           console.log(`  ${agent.feature_id}: failed — max retries reached (use 'wombo retry' to reset)`);\n187:         }\n188:         break;\n189:     }\n190:   }\n191: \n192:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n193: \n194:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n195:   // Phase 1: Parallel build verification\n196:   // Each agent's worktree is independent, so dep install + build can run\n197:   // concurrently. Merges must remain sequential (they mutate the project root).\n198:   // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n199:   if (toVerify.length > 0) {\n200:     console.log(`\\nVerifying ${toVerify.length} agent(s) in parallel...\\n`);\n201: \n202:     const verifyResults = await Promise.all(\n203:       toVerify.map(async (agent): Promise<{ agent: AgentState; needsMerge: boolean }> => {\n204:         const feature = featureMap.get(agent.feature_id);\n205:         if (!feature) return { agent, needsMerge: false };\n206: \n207:         // Already verified — skip build, go straight to merge\n208:         if (agent.status === \"verified\") {\n209:           printAgentUpdate(agent, \"already verified — queued for merge\");\n210:           return { agent, needsMerge: true };\n211:         }\n212: \n213:         printAgentUpdate(agent, \"verifying build...\");\n214: \n215:         // Ensure deps are installed — worktree may exist without node_modules\n216:         // (e.g., failed agents whose setup was interrupted)\n217:         if (!worktreeReady(agent.worktree) && worktreeExists(agent.worktree)) {\n218:           try {\n219:             printAgentUpdate(agent, \"installing deps...\");\n220:             await installDeps(agent.worktree, agent.feature_id, config);\n221:           } catch (depErr: any) {\n222:             printAgentUpdate(agent, `dep install failed: ${depErr.message}`);\n223:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n224:               status: \"failed\",\n225:               error: `Dependency install failed: ${depErr.message}`,\n226:               retries: agent.retries + 1,\n227:               completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n228:             });\n229:             saveState(projectRoot, state);\n230:             return { agent, needsMerge: false };\n231:           }\n232:         }\n233: \n234:         try {\n235:           const buildResult = await runBuild(agent.worktree, config);\n236:           if (buildResult.passed) {\n237:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n238:               status: \"verified\",\n239:               build_passed: true,\n240:               build_output: null,\n241:             });\n242:             saveState(projectRoot, state);\n243:             printAgentUpdate(agent, `BUILD PASSED (${Math.round(buildResult.durationMs / 1000)}s)`);\n244:             return { agent, needsMerge: true };\n245:           } else {\n246:             // Build failed\n247:             if (agent.retries < agent.max_retries) {\n248:               updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n249:                 status: \"retry\",\n250:                 retries: agent.retries + 1,\n251:                 build_passed: false,\n252:                 build_output: buildResult.errorSummary,\n253:               });\n254:               saveState(projectRoot, state);\n255:               printAgentUpdate(agent, `BUILD FAILED — will retry (${agent.retries + 1}/${agent.max_retries})`);\n256:             } else {\n257:               updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n258:                 status: \"failed\",\n259:                 build_passed: false,\n260:                 build_output: buildResult.errorSummary,\n261:                 error: `Build failed after ${agent.max_retries} retries`,\n262:                 completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n263:               });\n264:               saveState(projectRoot, state);\n265:               printAgentUpdate(agent, \"BUILD FAILED — max retries reached\");\n266:             }\n267:             return { agent, needsMerge: false };\n268:           }\n269:         } catch (err: any) {\n270:           printAgentUpdate(agent, `verify error: ${err.message}`);\n271:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n272:             status: \"failed\",\n273:             error: `Build verification error: ${err.message}`,\n274:             completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n275:           });\n276:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n277:           return { agent, needsMerge: false };\n278:         }\n279:       })\n280:     );\n281: \n282:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n283: \n284:     // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n285:     // Phase 2: Sequential merge for verified agents\n286:     // Merges must be sequential because they operate on the project root.\n287:     // -------------------------------------------------------------------------\n288:     const toMerge = verifyResults.filter((r) => r.needsMerge);\n289:     if (toMerge.length > 0) {\n290:       console.log(`\\nMerging ${toMerge.length} verified agent(s)...\\n`);\n291:       for (const { agent } of toMerge) {\n292:         const feature = featureMap.get(agent.feature_id);\n293:         if (!feature) continue;\n294:         try {\n295:           await attemptMerge(projectRoot, state, agent, feature, config, opts.model);\n296:         } catch (err: any) {\n297:           printAgentUpdate(agent, `merge error: ${err.message}`);\n298:         }\n299:       }\n300:     }\n301: \n302:     // Collect agents that need re-launching from verify results\n303:     for (const { agent } of verifyResults) {\n304:       if (agent.status === \"retry\" || agent.status === \"running\") {\n305:         toRelaunch.push(agent);\n306:       }\n307:     }\n308:   }\n309: \n310:   // Re-launch agents\n311:   const maxConcurrent = opts.maxConcurrent ?? state.max_concurrent;\n312:   const toLaunchNow = toRelaunch.slice(0, maxConcurrent);\n313:   if (toLaunchNow.length === 0) {\n314:     console.log(\"\\nNo agents need (re)launching.\");\n315:     printDashboard(state);\n316:     return;\n317:   }\n318: \n319:   console.log(`\\nRe-launching ${toLaunchNow.length} agent(s)...\\n`);\n320:   printDashboard(state);\n321: \n322:   const model = opts.model ?? state.model ?? undefined;\n323: \n324:   if (opts.interactive) {\n325:     // Interactive resume\n326:     await Promise.all(\n327:       toLaunchNow.map(async (agent) => {\n328:         const feature = featureMap.get(agent.feature_id);\n329:         if (!feature) return;\n330: \n331:         updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n332:           status: \"installing\",\n333:           started_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n334:           activity: \"resuming...\",\n335:         });\n336:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n337: \n338:         try {\n339:           if (!worktreeReady(agent.worktree)) {\n340:             await createWorktree(projectRoot, agent.feature_id, state.base_branch, config);\n341:             await installDeps(agent.worktree, agent.feature_id, config);\n342:           }\n343: \n344:           const prompt = generatePrompt(feature, state.base_branch, config);\n345:           const result = launchInteractive({\n346:             worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n347:             featureId: feature.id,\n348:             prompt,\n349:             model,\n350:             interactive: true,\n351:             config,\n352:           });\n353: \n354:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n355:             status: \"running\",\n356:             pid: result.pid,\n357:             activity: \"tmux session active\",\n358:           });\n359:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n360:         } catch (err: any) {\n361:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n362:             status: \"failed\",\n363:             error: err.message,\n364:             activity: null,\n365:             completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n366:           });\n367:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n368:         }\n369:       })\n370:     );\n371: \n372:     printDashboard(state);\n373:     console.log(`\\nResume complete. Use 'tmux attach -t ${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-<id>' to check sessions.`);\n374:   } else {\n375:     // Headless resume — re-enter monitoring loop\n376:     const monitor = new ProcessMonitor(projectRoot, {\n377:       onSessionId: (featureId, sessionId) => {\n378:         updateAgent(state, featureId, { session_id: sessionId });\n379:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n380:       },\n381:       onComplete: (featureId) => {\n382:         updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n383:           status: \"completed\",\n384:           completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n385:           activity: \"done\",\n386:         });\n387:         saveState(projectRoot, state);\n388:         wtLog(featureId, \"agent completed — verifying build...\");\n389: \n390:         const agent = state.agents.find((a) => a.feature_id === featureId)!;\n391:         const feature = featureMap.get(featureId)!;\n392:         handleBuildVerification(projectRoot, state, agent, feature, config, model, monitor)\n393:           .then(() => launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model))\n394:           .catch((err) => {\n395:             wtLog(featureId, `BUILD VERIFICATION UNHANDLED ERROR: ${err.message}`);\n396:             launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model);\n397:           });\n398:       },\n399:       onError: (featureId, error) => {\n400:         const agent = state.agents.find((a) => a.feature_id === featureId)!;\n401:         if (agent.retries < agent.max_retries) {\n402:           updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n403:             status: \"retry\",\n404:             retries: agent.retries + 1,\n405:             error,\n406:             activity: \"retrying...\",\n407:           });\n408:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n409:           handleRetry(projectRoot, state, agent, monitor, config, model);\n410:         } else {\n411:           updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n412:             status: \"failed\",\n413:             error,\n414:             activity: null,\n415:             completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n416:           });\n417:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n418:         }\n419:         launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model);\n420:       },\n421:       onActivity: (featureId, activity) => {\n422:         updateAgent(state, featureId, {\n423:           activity,\n424:           activity_updated_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n425:         });\n426:       },\n427:     });\n428: \n429:     // Handle graceful shutdown\n430:     const tuiRef = { current: null as WomboTUI | null };\n431:     process.on(\"SIGINT\", () => {\n432:       if (tuiRef.current) tuiRef.current.stop();\n433:       for (const agent of state.agents) {\n434:         if (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n435:           updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n436:             activity: \"interrupted\",\n437:           });\n438:         }\n439:       }\n440:       monitor.killAll();\n441:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n442:       console.log(\"\\nState saved. Use 'wombo resume' to continue.\");\n443:       process.exit(0);\n444:     });\n445: \n446:     await Promise.all(\n447:       toLaunchNow.map((agent) => {\n448:         const feature = featureMap.get(agent.feature_id);\n449:         if (!feature) return Promise.resolve();\n450:         return launchSingleHeadless(projectRoot, state, agent, feature, monitor, config, model);\n451:       })\n452:     );\n453: \n454:     // Start TUI dashboard (or skip if --no-tui)\n455:     if (!opts.noTui) {\n456:       tuiRef.current = new WomboTUI({\n457:         state,\n458:         monitor,\n459:         projectRoot,\n460:         interactive: false,\n461:         config,\n462:         onQuit: () => {\n463:           for (const agent of state.agents) {\n464:             if (agent.status === \"running\") {\n465:               updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, { activity: \"interrupted\" });\n466:             }\n467:           }\n468:           monitor.killAll();\n469:           saveState(projectRoot, state);\n470:           console.log(\"State saved. Use 'wombo resume' to continue.\");\n471:           process.exit(0);\n472:         },\n473:       });\n474:       tuiRef.current.start();\n475:     } else {\n476:       console.log(\"(--no-tui mode, dashboard prints every 15s)\\n\");\n477:       printDashboard(state);\n478:     }\n479: \n480:     // Monitoring loop\n481:     const POLL_INTERVAL = 5000;\n482:     let dashboardCounter = 0;\n483:     while (!isWaveComplete(state)) {\n484:       await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, POLL_INTERVAL));\n485: \n486:       for (const agent of state.agents) {\n487:         if (\n488:           (agent.status === \"running\" || agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") &&\n489:           agent.pid &&\n490:           !isProcessRunning(agent.pid) &&\n491:           !monitor.isRunning(agent.feature_id)\n492:         ) {\n493:           if (agent.status === \"resolving_conflict\") {\n494:             // Conflict resolver died unexpectedly — mark as failed\n495:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n496:               status: \"failed\",\n497:               error: \"Conflict resolver process died unexpectedly\",\n498:               activity: null,\n499:               completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n500:             });\n501:             saveState(projectRoot, state);\n502:             wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"conflict resolver died — marked failed\");\n503:             launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model);\n504:             continue;\n505:           }\n506:           // Check if the agent actually made any commits\n507:           if (!branchHasChanges(projectRoot, agent.branch, state.base_branch)) {\n508:             // Agent died without producing any code — mark as failed\n509:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n510:               status: \"failed\",\n511:               error: \"Agent process exited without making any commits\",\n512:               activity: null,\n513:               completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n514:             });\n515:             saveState(projectRoot, state);\n516:             wtLog(agent.feature_id, \"process died with no code changes — marked failed\");\n517:           } else {\n518:             updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n519:               status: \"completed\",\n520:               completed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n521:               activity: \"done\",\n522:             });\n523:             saveState(projectRoot, state);\n524:             const feature = featureMap.get(agent.feature_id)!;\n525:             try {\n526:               await handleBuildVerification(projectRoot, state, agent, feature, config, model, monitor);\n527:             } catch (err: any) {\n528:               wtLog(agent.feature_id, `POLL VERIFY ERROR: ${err.message}`);\n529:             }\n530:           }\n531:           launchNextQueued(projectRoot, state, featureMap, monitor, config, model);\n532:         }\n533:       }\n534: \n535:       saveState(projectRoot, state);\n536:       if (tuiRef.current) {\n537:         tuiRef.current.updateState(state);\n538:       } else if (opts.noTui) {\n539:         dashboardCounter++;\n540:         if (dashboardCounter % 3 === 0) {\n541:           printDashboard(state);\n542:         }\n543:       }\n544:     }\n545: \n546:     if (tuiRef.current) tuiRef.current.stop();\n547:     printDashboard(state);\n548: \n549:     // Auto-push base branch if requested\n550:     if (opts.autoPush) {\n551:       await pushBaseBranch(projectRoot, state.base_branch, config);\n552:     }\n553: \n554:     console.log(\"Wave complete.\");\n555:   }\n556: }\n\n(End of file - total 556 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/resume.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * resume.ts — Resume a previously stopped wave.\n *\n * Usage: wombo resume [options]\n *\n * Restores from .wombo-state.json:\n *   - Agents in \"running\"/\"installing\" whose PID is dead → re-check or re-launch\n *   - Agents in \"queued\" → launch them\n *   - Agents in terminal states (verified/failed/merged) → leave alone\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport type { Feature } from \"../lib/features.js\";\nimport { loadFeatures } from \"../lib/features.js\";\nimport {\n  loadState,\n  saveState,\n  updateAgent,\n  queuedAgents,\n  isWaveComplete,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351529082,"end":1773351529085}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351529401,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fcea7b001R72VG9oE1He0db","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_0176B3rtoojqTsFm5Ym4GJ1E","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/retry.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/retry.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * retry.ts — Retry a specific failed agent.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage: wombo retry <feature-id> [--interactive] [--model <model>]\n5:  *\n6:  * Resets the agent's retry count and re-launches it. Can launch in either\n7:  * headless mode (default) or interactive (tmux) mode.\n8:  */\n9: \n10: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n11: import { loadFeatures, type Feature } from \"../lib/features.js\";\n12: import {\n13:   loadState,\n14:   saveState,\n15:   updateAgent,\n16: } from \"../lib/state.js\";\n17: import { worktreeReady } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\n18: import { generatePrompt } from \"../lib/prompt.js\";\n19: import { launchInteractive } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\n20: import { ProcessMonitor } from \"../lib/monitor.js\";\n21: import { launchSingleHeadless } from \"./launch.js\";\n22: \n23: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n24: // Types\n25: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n26: \n27: export interface RetryCommandOptions {\n28:   projectRoot: string;\n29:   config: WomboConfig;\n30:   featureId: string;\n31:   model?: string;\n32:   interactive: boolean;\n33:   dryRun?: boolean;\n34: }\n35: \n36: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n37: // Command\n38: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n39: \n40: export async function cmdRetry(opts: RetryCommandOptions): Promise<void> {\n41:   const { projectRoot, config } = opts;\n42: \n43:   if (!opts.featureId) {\n44:     console.error(\"Usage: wombo retry <feature-id>\");\n45:     process.exit(1);\n46:     return; // unreachable — helps TypeScript narrow\n47:   }\n48: \n49:   const state = loadState(projectRoot);\n50:   if (!state) {\n51:     console.log(\"No active wave.\");\n52:     return;\n53:   }\n54: \n55:   const agent = state.agents.find((a) => a.feature_id === opts.featureId);\n56:   if (!agent) {\n57:     console.error(`Agent not found for feature: ${opts.featureId}`);\n58:     process.exit(1);\n59:     return; // unreachable — helps TypeScript narrow\n60:   }\n61: \n62:   if (agent.status !== \"failed\") {\n63:     console.error(\n64:       `Agent ${opts.featureId} is not in failed state (current: ${agent.status})`\n65:     );\n66:     process.exit(1);\n67:     return; // unreachable — helps TypeScript narrow\n68:   }\n69: \n70:   // Dry-run: show what would be retried without doing it\n71:   if (opts.dryRun) {\n72:     console.log(`\\n[dry-run] Would retry agent: ${opts.featureId}`);\n73:     console.log(`  Current status: ${agent.status}`);\n74:     console.log(`  Retries so far: ${agent.retries}`);\n75:     console.log(`  Worktree: ${agent.worktree}`);\n76:     console.log(`  Mode: ${opts.interactive ? \"interactive (tmux)\" : \"headless\"}`);\n77:     if (opts.model) console.log(`  Model: ${opts.model}`);\n78:     return;\n79:   }\n80: \n81:   // Reset retry count and re-run\n82:   updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n83:     status: \"queued\",\n84:     retries: 0,\n85:     error: null,\n86:     build_passed: null,\n87:     build_output: null,\n88:     completed_at: null,\n89:   });\n90:   saveState(projectRoot, state);\n91: \n92:   const data = loadFeatures(projectRoot, config);\n93:   const feature = data.features.find((f) => f.id === opts.featureId);\n94:   if (!feature) {\n95:     console.error(`Feature ${opts.featureId} not found in ${config.featuresFile}`);\n96:     process.exit(1);\n97:     return; // unreachable — helps TypeScript narrow\n98:   }\n99: \n100:   if (opts.interactive) {\n101:     const prompt = generatePrompt(feature, state.base_branch, config);\n102:     launchInteractive({\n103:       worktreePath: agent.worktree,\n104:       featureId: feature.id,\n105:       prompt,\n106:       model: opts.model,\n107:       interactive: true,\n108:       config,\n109:     });\n110: \n111:     updateAgent(state, agent.feature_id, {\n112:       status: \"running\",\n113:       started_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n114:     });\n115:     saveState(projectRoot, state);\n116:     console.log(`Retrying ${opts.featureId} in tmux session ${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-${opts.featureId}`);\n117:   } else {\n118:     const monitor = new ProcessMonitor(projectRoot);\n119:     await launchSingleHeadless(projectRoot, state, agent, feature, monitor, config, opts.model);\n120:     console.log(`Retrying ${opts.featureId} in headless mode`);\n121:   }\n122: }\n\n(End of file - total 122 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/retry.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * retry.ts — Retry a specific failed agent.\n *\n * Usage: wombo retry <feature-id> [--interactive] [--model <model>]\n *\n * Resets the agent's retry count and re-launches it. Can launch in either\n * headless mode (default) or interactive (tmux) mode.\n */\n\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport { loadFeatures, type Feature } from \"../lib/features.js\";\nimport {\n  loadState,\n  saveState,\n  updateAgent,\n} from \"../lib/state.js\";\nimport { worktreeReady } from \"../lib/worktree.js\";\nimport { generatePrompt } from \"../lib/prompt.js\";\nimport { launchInteractive } from \"../lib/launcher.js\";\nimport { ProcessMonitor } from \"../lib/monitor.js\";","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351529398,"end":1773351529401}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773351529855,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fcec20001wd7fhZZzITKcvT","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce3fccd4f001DufgT2kP7sAWzP","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_019EX6iVeKAKNvq4vyKMsKyZ","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/upgrade.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-json-output-complete/src/commands/upgrade.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * upgrade.ts — Self-upgrade wombo from GitHub.\n3:  *\n4:  * Usage:\n5:  *   wombo upgrade              # Check for updates and prompt to install\n6:  *   wombo upgrade --force      # Skip confirmation prompt\n7:  *   wombo upgrade --version v0.1.0  # Install a specific version\n8:  *   wombo upgrade --check      # Only check, don't install\n9:  */\n10: \n11: import { readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\n12: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n13: import { createInterface } from \"node:readline\";\n14: \n15: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n16: // Types\n17: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n18: \n19: export interface UpgradeOptions {\n20:   force: boolean;\n21:   version?: string;\n22:   checkOnly: boolean;\n23: }\n24: \n25: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n26: // Helpers\n27: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n28: \n29: const REPO = \"fulgidus/wombo\";\n30: \n31: /**\n32:  * Get the locally installed version from package.json.\n33:  * Uses import.meta to find the package.json relative to this source file,\n34:  * which works whether running from local source or global install.\n35:  */\n36: function getLocalVersion(): string {\n37:   const pkgPath = resolve(import.meta.dir, \"../../package.json\");\n38:   const raw = readFileSync(pkgPath, \"utf-8\");\n39:   return JSON.parse(raw).version as string;\n40: }\n41: \n42: /**\n43:  * Fetch all v* tags from the remote GitHub repo using git ls-remote.\n44:  * Returns tags sorted by semver descending (latest first).\n45:  */\n46: async function fetchRemoteTags(): Promise<string[]> {\n47:   const proc = Bun.spawn([\"git\", \"ls-remote\", \"--tags\", `https://github.com/${REPO}.git`], {\n48:     stdout: \"pipe\",\n49:     stderr: \"pipe\",\n50:   });\n51: \n52:   const stdout = await new Response(proc.stdout).text();\n53:   const exitCode = await proc.exited;\n54: \n55:   if (exitCode !== 0) {\n56:     const stderr = await new Response(proc.stderr).text();\n57:     throw new Error(`Failed to fetch remote tags: ${stderr.trim()}`);\n58:   }\n59: \n60:   // Parse lines like: \"abc123\\trefs/tags/v0.0.1\"\n61:   const tags: string[] = [];\n62:   for (const line of stdout.split(\"\\n\")) {\n63:     const match = line.match(/refs\\/tags\\/(v\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+)$/);\n64:     if (match) {\n65:       tags.push(match[1]);\n66:     }\n67:   }\n68: \n69:   // Sort descending by semver\n70:   tags.sort((a, b) => {\n71:     const pa = a.slice(1).split(\".\").map(Number);\n72:     const pb = b.slice(1).split(\".\").map(Number);\n73:     for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {\n74:       if (pa[i] !== pb[i]) return pb[i] - pa[i];\n75:     }\n76:     return 0;\n77:   });\n78: \n79:   return tags;\n80: }\n81: \n82: /**\n83:  * Compare two semver strings. Returns:\n84:  *   -1 if a < b\n85:  *    0 if a === b\n86:  *    1 if a > b\n87:  */\n88: function compareSemver(a: string, b: string): number {\n89:   const pa = a.replace(/^v/, \"\").split(\".\").map(Number);\n90:   const pb = b.replace(/^v/, \"\").split(\".\").map(Number);\n91:   for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {\n92:     if (pa[i] < pb[i]) return -1;\n93:     if (pa[i] > pb[i]) return 1;\n94:   }\n95:   return 0;\n96: }\n97: \n98: /**\n99:  * Prompt the user for yes/no confirmation.\n100:  */\n101: async function confirm(message: string): Promise<boolean> {\n102:   if (!process.stdin.isTTY) return false;\n103: \n104:   const rl = createInterface({ input: process.stdin, output: process.stdout });\n105:   return new Promise<boolean>((resolve) => {\n106:     rl.question(`${message} [y/N] `, (answer) => {\n107:       rl.close();\n108:       resolve(answer.trim().toLowerCase() === \"y\");\n109:     });\n110:   });\n111: }\n112: \n113: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n114: // Command\n115: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n116: \n117: export async function cmdUpgrade(opts: UpgradeOptions): Promise<void> {\n118:   const localVersion = getLocalVersion();\n119:   console.log(`Current version: v${localVersion}`);\n120: \n121:   // If a specific version is requested, skip the check\n122:   if (opts.version) {\n123:     const targetTag = opts.version.startsWith(\"v\") ? opts.version : `v${opts.version}`;\n124:     console.log(`Requested version: ${targetTag}`);\n125: \n126:     if (compareSemver(localVersion, targetTag) === 0) {\n127:       console.log(\"Already at the requested version.\");\n128:       return;\n129:     }\n130: \n131:     if (!opts.force) {\n132:       const ok = await confirm(`Install ${targetTag}?`);\n133:       if (!ok) {\n134:         console.log(\"Upgrade cancelled.\");\n135:         return;\n136:       }\n137:     }\n138: \n139:     await installVersion(targetTag);\n140:     return;\n141:   }\n142: \n143:   // Fetch latest from GitHub\n144:   console.log(`Checking for updates from github.com/${REPO}...`);\n145: \n146:   let tags: string[];\n147:   try {\n148:     tags = await fetchRemoteTags();\n149:   } catch (err: any) {\n150:     console.error(`Failed to check for updates: ${err.message}`);\n151:     process.exit(1);\n152:     return;\n153:   }\n154: \n155:   if (tags.length === 0) {\n156:     console.error(\"No release tags found on the remote repository.\");\n157:     process.exit(1);\n158:     return;\n159:   }\n160: \n161:   const latestTag = tags[0];\n162:   const latestVersion = latestTag.slice(1); // strip 'v'\n163:   console.log(`Latest version:  ${latestTag}`);\n164: \n165:   const cmp = compareSemver(localVersion, latestVersion);\n166:   if (cmp >= 0) {\n167:     console.log(\"You are already up to date.\");\n168:     return;\n169:   }\n170: \n171:   if (opts.checkOnly) {\n172:     console.log(`\\nUpdate available: v${localVersion} → ${latestTag}`);\n173:     console.log(`Run 'wombo upgrade' to install.`);\n174:     return;\n175:   }\n176: \n177:   console.log(`\\nUpdate available: v${localVersion} → ${latestTag}`);\n178: \n179:   if (!opts.force) {\n180:     const ok = await confirm(`Upgrade to ${latestTag}?`);\n181:     if (!ok) {\n182:       console.log(\"Upgrade cancelled.\");\n183:       return;\n184:     }\n185:   }\n186: \n187:   await installVersion(latestTag);\n188: }\n189: \n190: async function installVersion(tag: string): Promise<void> {\n191:   console.log(`\\nInstalling wombo@${tag}...`);\n192: \n193:   const proc = Bun.spawn(\n194:     [\"bun\", \"install\", \"-g\", `github:${REPO}#${tag}`],\n195:     {\n196:       stdout: \"inherit\",\n197:       stderr: \"inherit\",\n198:     }\n199:   );\n200: \n201:   const exitCode = await proc.exited;\n202: \n203:   if (exitCode !== 0) {\n204:     console.error(`\\nInstallation failed (exit code ${exitCode}).`);\n205:     process.exit(1);\n206:     return;\n207:   }\n208: \n209:   console.log(`\\nSuccessfully upgraded to ${tag}.`);\n210: }\n\n(End of file - total 210 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/commands/upgrade.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * upgrade.ts — Self-upgrade wombo from GitHub.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   wombo upgrade              # Check for updates and prompt to install\n *   wombo upgrade --force      # Skip confirmation prompt\n *   wombo upgrade --version v0.1.0  # Install a specific version\n *   wombo upgrade --check      # Only check, don't install\n */\n\nimport { readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { resolve } from \"node:path\";\nimport { createInterface } from \"node:readline\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Types\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface UpgradeOptions {\n  force: boolean;","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773351529852,"end":1773351529854}}}}
