{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351983270,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","part":{"id":"prt_ce403b8be002JYmmBu7wwy6YXI","sessionID":"ses_31c036d66ffeb3gOzUVP7hTP5i","messageID":"msg_ce403b145001iddQxw1kXHQYc1","type":"text","text":"Everything is clean and committed. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe feature `json-output-complete` is fully implemented across **2 commits**:\n\n### Commit 1: `feat(json-output-complete): retrofit features check and archive with --output json`\n- **`features check`** — Outputs `{ok, issues, errors, warnings, items_checked}` in JSON mode\n- **`features archive`** — Outputs `{archived: [{id, title, status}], count}` in JSON mode\n\n### Commit 2: `feat(json-output-complete): retrofit all operational commands with --output json`\n- **`status`** — Emits full wave state with agent details (`{wave_id, base_branch, counts, agents}`)\n- **`launch`** — JSON for dry-run and error paths; live TUI/monitoring stays text-only\n- **`cleanup`** — JSON for both dry-run inventory and execution results\n- **`verify`** — JSON with per-agent build verification results\n- **`merge`** — JSON with per-branch merge results and push status\n- **`resume`** — JSON for error paths; live monitoring stays text-only\n- **`retry`** — JSON for dry-run, error, and success paths\n- **`upgrade`** — JSON for version check, install, and error paths\n- **`index.ts`** — All switch cases now pass `outputFmt`; retry uses `outputError` instead of raw `console.error` + `process.exit`\n\n### Key design decisions:\n- Human-friendly text output remains the default (no breaking change)\n- Interactive/long-running commands (launch monitoring, resume monitoring) stay text-only for the live parts — JSON is used for initial responses, dry-run, and error exits\n- All commands use the shared `output()`, `outputError()`, and `outputMessage()` helpers from `src/lib/output.ts`\n- TypeScript typecheck and build both pass cleanly","time":{"start":1773351983269,"end":1773351983269}}}
